def _get_time_bins(self, ax):
        from pandas import DatetimeIndex, date_range, NaT
        from pandas.core.arrays.datetimes import DatetimeArray
        ax_values = ax.asi8
        binner, bin_edges = self._adjust_bin_edges(DatetimeIndex(data=[], freq=self.freq, name=ax.name), ax_values)

        # general version, knowing nothing about relative frequencies
        bins = DatetimeArray._generate_bin_edges(ax_values, bin_edges, closed=self.closed, hasnans=ax.hasnans)

        if self.closed == "right" and self.label == "right":
            labels = binner[1:]
        else:
            labels = binner

        if ax.hasnans:
            labels = labels.insert(0, NaT)

        # if we end up with more labels than bins
        # adjust the labels
        # GH4076
        if len(bins) < len(labels):
            labels = labels[: len(bins)]

        return binner, bins, labels
